WEBVTT

00:00.570 --> 00:06.000 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
♪ ♪

00:34.230 --> 00:40.970 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
♪ ♪

00:40.970 --> 00:44.330 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> During the summer, my uncle
asked me if I wanted to go,

00:44.330 --> 00:48.870 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
like, learn the job
that he was doing.

00:48.870 --> 00:53.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
My mom wanted me to go so
that I can see how hard it is

00:53.270 --> 00:56.230 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
to work out in the sun.

00:56.230 --> 00:58.870 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
What they did was, like,
just started a house

00:58.870 --> 01:01.970 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
from the bottom to the top.

01:01.970 --> 01:04.530 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I always like working with my
hands or just,

01:04.530 --> 01:07.500 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
like, learning new things.

01:07.500 --> 01:09.330 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
♪ ♪

01:09.330 --> 01:13.400 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Then that day that we were
heading back, I was on my phone.

01:13.400 --> 01:16.870 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
And, Hector, he starts saying
that, "Nah, there's...

01:16.870 --> 01:18.500 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
the cops are coming."

01:18.500 --> 01:21.130 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
(chatter on police radio)

01:21.130 --> 01:24.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
So, my uncle pulls over,
and all he tells us is,

01:24.100 --> 01:26.970 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
"Just relax, nothing's wrong."

01:26.970 --> 01:30.530 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
(chatter on police radio)

01:30.530 --> 01:34.030 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
The cop came, started asking
for our papers,

01:34.030 --> 01:36.300 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
if we had any identification,
everything.

01:36.300 --> 01:37.600 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> POLICE OFFICER:

01:37.600 --> 01:39.700 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> Yeah.

01:52.700 --> 01:54.870 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> He took me, out he made me
talk to Border Patrol.

01:54.870 --> 01:56.870 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> BORDER PATROL AND MARTIN:

02:00.970 --> 02:03.200 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> BORDER PATROL:

02:03.200 --> 02:04.400 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> MARTIN:

02:05.500 --> 02:07.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
We were all handcuffed.

02:07.270 --> 02:10.130 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
And I started asking the cops,
like, "What's happening,

02:10.130 --> 02:11.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
what are they going
to do to us?"

02:11.630 --> 02:14.800 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
And he just told us that we
weren't supposed to be here,

02:14.800 --> 02:16.870 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and because we were illegal,
Border Patrol was going

02:16.870 --> 02:21.600 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
to come get us.

02:21.600 --> 02:25.900 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
As soon as I was in the back
of the car,

02:25.900 --> 02:28.670 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I-I just felt like everything
was over.

02:31.400 --> 02:35.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
♪ ♪

02:40.670 --> 02:44.130 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> DAFFODIL ALTAN:
That night in June 2019

02:44.130 --> 02:46.400 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
was the beginning of a long
journey for Martin.

02:46.400 --> 02:51.030 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
It would land him hundreds of
miles from home.

02:51.030 --> 02:54.600 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> Have you ever been to a
stadium?

02:54.600 --> 02:56.830 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
It was like a stadium but with
cages inside,

02:56.830 --> 02:59.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and that's where they kept
all the people.

02:59.630 --> 03:03.000 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
And when we walked in there, we
just saw people, it's like,

03:03.000 --> 03:06.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
crying, we saw little kids
crying.

03:06.100 --> 03:07.400 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
They put me in the cage.

03:07.400 --> 03:10.170 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I was with around
12 other younger minors.

03:10.170 --> 03:12.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I didn't really know what
to think, I was like,

03:12.270 --> 03:16.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
"Is this prison,
or, like, what is this?"

03:16.100 --> 03:18.500 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I kind of broke down.

03:18.500 --> 03:20.470 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I didn't know what to do.

03:20.470 --> 03:22.330 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: He had ended up
in a massive

03:22.330 --> 03:26.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
U.S. Border Patrol holding pen
in McAllen, Texas.

03:26.100 --> 03:28.730 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> A bleak picture of conditions
for migrant children.

03:28.730 --> 03:31.130 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> We are seeing sick children,
we are seeing dirty children,

03:31.130 --> 03:32.730 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
we are seeing hungry children...

03:32.730 --> 03:36.400 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ...say there is not enough
food, water, or sanitation.

03:36.400 --> 03:37.770 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Martin had spent most
of his life

03:37.770 --> 03:40.500 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
in the U.S.,
but it didn't matter.

03:40.500 --> 03:42.700 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Like tens of thousands of kids
who had recently crossed

03:42.700 --> 03:44.170 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
the border on their own,

03:44.170 --> 03:46.070 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
or had been separated
from their parents,

03:46.070 --> 03:48.900 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
he was handed over to
a federal agency,

03:48.900 --> 03:51.830 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
the Department of Health
and Human Services.

03:51.830 --> 03:53.930 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> MARTHA MENDOZA: When a child
arrives at the U.S. border,

03:53.930 --> 03:55.370 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
they are taken into custody

03:55.370 --> 03:57.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
by U.S. Customs and Border
Protection,

03:57.270 --> 04:02.230 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
whose mission is to protect the
security of the United States.

04:02.230 --> 04:04.400 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
They're not set up to take care
of anybody.

04:04.400 --> 04:05.930 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
They then turn that child over

04:05.930 --> 04:08.400 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
to the U.S. Department of Health
and Human Services,

04:08.400 --> 04:12.430 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
which is an agency whose mission
is to take care of people.

04:12.430 --> 04:15.570 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
♪ ♪

04:15.570 --> 04:17.800 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: I've been reporting
on the lives

04:17.800 --> 04:22.370 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
of undocumented people in
America for the past decade.

04:22.370 --> 04:24.770 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> These kids are getting sent
all around the country...

04:24.770 --> 04:26.400 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN:
With the Associated Press,

04:26.400 --> 04:29.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
we've been investigating HHS's
detention system

04:29.100 --> 04:30.700 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
for migrant children.

04:30.700 --> 04:32.500 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> GARANCE BURKE: We're going
to end up with sort of like

04:32.500 --> 04:35.230 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
a generation of migrant kids
who are going to have

04:35.230 --> 04:38.430 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
this kind of lasting trauma.

04:38.430 --> 04:40.770 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: My partners
at the A.P.,

04:40.770 --> 04:44.000 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
investigative reporters Garance
Burke and Martha Mendoza,

04:44.000 --> 04:46.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
have been on this story
for years.

04:46.630 --> 04:49.370 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
They obtained confidential
HHS data

04:49.370 --> 04:51.970 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
showing where migrant children
are being held

04:51.970 --> 04:55.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and how many of them are in
detention at any given time.

04:55.630 --> 04:57.600 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> BURKE: What we found in our
reporting

04:57.600 --> 05:01.430 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
is that never before had there
been this many children

05:01.430 --> 05:05.030 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
held inside the government's
network of shelters

05:05.030 --> 05:06.870 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
for migrant kids.

05:06.870 --> 05:09.570 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
The majority of those kids were
in facilities

05:09.570 --> 05:13.800 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
with more than 100
or 1,000 other children,

05:13.800 --> 05:17.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
so mass facilities where,
psychiatrists say,

05:17.630 --> 05:21.570 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
kids start to feel like
just another number.

05:21.570 --> 05:25.400 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: HHS's own numbers now
show that over the past year,

05:25.400 --> 05:27.830 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
nearly 70,000 migrant children
have been held

05:27.830 --> 05:31.430 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
without their parents-- more
than any other time on record--

05:31.430 --> 05:33.830 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and more than any other country
in the world.

05:33.830 --> 05:35.430 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
♪ ♪

05:35.430 --> 05:39.930 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
One of HHS's largest facilities
is an emergency influx shelter

05:39.930 --> 05:42.130 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
in Homestead, Florida.

05:42.130 --> 05:45.470 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
That's where Martin ended up
in June 2019.

05:45.470 --> 05:49.070 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
At the time, nearly one out of
every five migrant kids

05:49.070 --> 05:52.000 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
in HHS custody
was being held there.

05:52.000 --> 05:53.930 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> When we arrived there,
you could just see

05:53.930 --> 05:58.500 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
there was a couple of guards,
armed guards, by the entrance.

05:58.500 --> 06:01.300 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Once we went inside,
we saw kids playing outside,

06:01.300 --> 06:04.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
there was kids playing soccer.

06:04.100 --> 06:06.170 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
In my head, what I was thinking
was, like,

06:06.170 --> 06:08.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
"This was a way better place
than where I was,

06:08.270 --> 06:11.300 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
in Immigration."

06:11.300 --> 06:13.200 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
But this place
is not really home,

06:13.200 --> 06:16.400 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
so I didn't really feel safe
at the same time.

06:16.400 --> 06:18.730 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: There were more than
2,000 teenagers

06:18.730 --> 06:21.000 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
being held at Homestead.

06:21.000 --> 06:22.900 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> With very high numbers
of children

06:22.900 --> 06:25.030 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
coming across the border
at times,

06:25.030 --> 06:28.230 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
HHS has to be able to meet
its responsibility,

06:28.230 --> 06:30.470 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
both legally and morally,
to have a place

06:30.470 --> 06:31.870 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
for these children to go.

06:31.870 --> 06:35.270 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
And I would say that, you know,
even one of our influx shelters

06:35.270 --> 06:38.430 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
is better than a CBP
processing center.

06:38.430 --> 06:40.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Jonathan Hayes
is the director

06:40.630 --> 06:42.670 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
of the Office of Refugee
Resettlement,

06:42.670 --> 06:45.170 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
which is legally required to
care for migrant children

06:45.170 --> 06:47.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
within HHS.

06:47.100 --> 06:49.670 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
He sat down with the A.P.'s
Garance Burke.

06:49.670 --> 06:52.230 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> BURKE: So, why would your
agency hold

06:52.230 --> 06:55.300 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
so many children together,
both in influx shelters

06:55.300 --> 06:57.730 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and just very large shelters?

06:57.730 --> 06:59.730 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> There were some periods where
we were receiving

06:59.730 --> 07:02.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
400 to 500 kids every day.

07:02.630 --> 07:06.470 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
You know, you-you may look at a,
at a shelter with 500 kids,

07:06.470 --> 07:07.900 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and realize, "I could fill up
one of those in one day,

07:07.900 --> 07:09.900 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
potentially."

07:09.900 --> 07:12.670 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: HHS would not allow us
to bring cameras

07:12.670 --> 07:16.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
inside Homestead, despite
repeated requests.

07:16.100 --> 07:19.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
But over the past year,
we've spoken to numerous kids

07:19.100 --> 07:22.930 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
who've been detained--
including this girl,

07:22.930 --> 07:25.000 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
who says spent a month
and a half inside Homestead

07:25.000 --> 07:27.970 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
waiting to be reunited
with her father.

07:27.970 --> 07:30.070 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
She asked us to disguise
her voice out of concerns

07:30.070 --> 07:32.430 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
for her immigration status.

07:32.430 --> 07:36.770 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> GIRL (speaking Spanish):

07:46.000 --> 07:48.800 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: She says most of the
day was spent in classrooms,

07:48.800 --> 07:51.670 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
with only one hour
of outdoor time.

08:17.900 --> 08:20.200 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: The mass detention of
children at Homestead

08:20.200 --> 08:23.470 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and other HHS sites stems
in part

08:23.470 --> 08:27.730 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
from a little-known decision by
the Trump administration.

08:27.730 --> 08:32.000 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
In 2018 HHS started doing
extensive background checks

08:32.000 --> 08:34.570 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
on the children's sponsors,
mostly relatives

08:34.570 --> 08:37.230 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
trying to claim them
from detention.

08:37.230 --> 08:39.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> MENDOZA: They began vetting
sponsors and families

08:39.270 --> 08:41.130 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
to the extreme.

08:41.130 --> 08:43.600 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Anybody in a house where these
kids were going to go to

08:43.600 --> 08:46.400 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
would have to be fingerprinted,
background checked,

08:46.400 --> 08:50.700 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and fully screened,
which took a long time.

08:50.700 --> 08:53.000 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: While the extreme
vetting was in effect,

08:53.000 --> 08:55.730 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
the time kids were spending in
HHS shelters

08:55.730 --> 08:58.970 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
went from a few weeks to months.

08:58.970 --> 09:02.230 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> Some of the additional
changes that did come to be,

09:02.230 --> 09:05.930 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I think did have an impact
on kind of slowing down

09:05.930 --> 09:07.570 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
the, you know, the process in
that.

09:07.570 --> 09:09.900 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
But, you know, it's always
a balance between,

09:09.900 --> 09:11.530 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
you know, the safety
of the children,

09:11.530 --> 09:13.970 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
but also being able to discharge
them as quickly

09:13.970 --> 09:16.200 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
but as safely as possible.

09:16.200 --> 09:21.070 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
♪ ♪

09:21.070 --> 09:23.800 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: In Florida
this past summer,

09:23.800 --> 09:25.600 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
we met a woman who had been
trying to get her nephew

09:25.600 --> 09:28.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
out of Homestead.

09:28.100 --> 09:30.430 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> XIOMARA (speaking Spanish):

09:35.500 --> 09:39.170 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Xiomara says her
16-year-old nephew Jarin

09:39.170 --> 09:42.170 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
left Honduras because gangs
were trying to recruit him.

09:56.700 --> 09:59.100 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Though she herself is
undocumented,

09:59.100 --> 10:02.500 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Xiomara says she gave HHS
everything they asked for,

10:02.500 --> 10:06.070 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
but Jarin had been in detention
for almost four months.

10:18.230 --> 10:20.400 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
♪ ♪

10:44.070 --> 10:45.470 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN:

10:46.330 --> 10:50.800 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> XIOMARA:

10:57.800 --> 10:59.870 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Along with the extreme
vetting,

10:59.870 --> 11:01.970 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
we found there was another
factor pushing up the number

11:01.970 --> 11:03.930 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
of kids in detention:

11:03.930 --> 11:07.030 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
HHS was sharing information
with ICE

11:07.030 --> 11:10.430 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
about sponsors coming to claim
their children.

11:10.430 --> 11:15.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> What it was meant to do was
to cast a larger net

11:15.100 --> 11:17.430 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
after those that could be
particularly targeted

11:17.430 --> 11:19.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
for apprehensions.

11:19.100 --> 11:22.570 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Andrew Lorenzen Strait
was a deputy assistant director

11:22.570 --> 11:24.330 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
of ICE at the time.

11:24.330 --> 11:26.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
In May 2018 he helped write
the agreement

11:26.630 --> 11:28.500 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
between the two agencies.

11:28.500 --> 11:33.630 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> I thought we were going to be
looking at how we care for kids

11:33.630 --> 11:38.130 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
that may have these issues of
being taken advantage of--

11:38.130 --> 11:40.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
trafficked, smuggled.

11:40.270 --> 11:42.500 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Instead,
ICE used the information

11:42.500 --> 11:44.530 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
to apprehend sponsors.

11:44.530 --> 11:46.400 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
In the months following
the agreement,

11:46.400 --> 11:50.670 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
the agency says around
330 people were arrested.

11:50.670 --> 11:54.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> There is a total chilling
effect of coming forward,

11:54.100 --> 11:58.000 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
because they believe they are
going to be picked up by ICE.

11:58.000 --> 12:01.470 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
The outcomes of that partnership
were devastating

12:01.470 --> 12:03.900 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
to the migrant community.

12:03.900 --> 12:05.830 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> BURKE: In some of the
government paperwork I've seen,

12:05.830 --> 12:09.130 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
there are fewer sponsors
coming forward now,

12:09.130 --> 12:12.930 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and that that's led to more
children being in custody.

12:12.930 --> 12:16.600 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> I have absolutely heard some
anecdotal conversations

12:16.600 --> 12:18.600 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and comments, you know,
that there, you know,

12:18.600 --> 12:22.970 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
there was some examples of
sponsors that were concerned.

12:22.970 --> 12:27.870 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
However, I-I really reject, you
know, the-the very premise

12:27.870 --> 12:31.730 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
that there's this very
widespread pattern.

12:31.730 --> 12:33.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: ICE says it's not
arresting people

12:33.270 --> 12:35.370 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
in this way anymore.

12:35.370 --> 12:37.300 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
But the fear remains.

12:37.300 --> 12:40.070 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
At her home in Texas, Martin's
mother was worried

12:40.070 --> 12:44.130 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
about being arrested as she
searched for her son.

12:44.130 --> 12:46.970 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> WOMAN:

13:41.000 --> 13:43.170 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Martin was born in
Mexico

13:43.170 --> 13:46.330 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and brought to the U.S. when he
was nine months old.

13:46.330 --> 13:50.400 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> WOMAN:

14:03.670 --> 14:05.700 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: But even undocumented
kids like him,

14:05.700 --> 14:11.000 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
who've been here most of their
lives, have been detained.

14:11.000 --> 14:12.930 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> WOMAN:

14:24.270 --> 14:26.330 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: As more children
were being held,

14:26.330 --> 14:28.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and for longer times,

14:28.270 --> 14:30.470 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
we began hearing from human
rights advocates

14:30.470 --> 14:34.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and mental health experts
who'd been inside Homestead.

14:34.270 --> 14:36.570 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> Never have I ever been
to a facility

14:36.570 --> 14:42.500 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
that has 2,000-plus children
in one place.

14:42.500 --> 14:45.970 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
It's a, it's a deeply
unnatural state.

14:45.970 --> 14:47.830 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
We've been monitoring facilities
all over the...

14:47.830 --> 14:50.900 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Neha Desai is part
of a group of attorneys

14:50.900 --> 14:53.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
who monitor the conditions for
migrant children

14:53.270 --> 14:55.170 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
inside detention facilities.

14:55.170 --> 14:56.530 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> That are deteriorating...

14:56.530 --> 15:00.130 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
What we know from decades and
decades of research

15:00.130 --> 15:02.670 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
is the way we should treat
these kids

15:02.670 --> 15:05.700 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
is in the most homelike setting,

15:05.700 --> 15:08.830 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
in the least restrictive setting
possible.

15:08.830 --> 15:11.800 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Children at Homestead are
monitored 24-seven

15:11.800 --> 15:14.030 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
by security guards.

15:14.030 --> 15:17.330 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Children tell me that
they can't walk five feet

15:17.330 --> 15:20.030 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
to go to the bathroom
by themselves.

15:20.030 --> 15:23.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
These children are not free
to leave.

15:23.630 --> 15:25.830 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Psychologist Yenys
Castillo was brought

15:25.830 --> 15:29.930 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
into Homestead to assess
the impact of detention.

15:29.930 --> 15:31.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> All of the children in
Homestead said,

15:31.630 --> 15:34.400 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
"We are prisoners;
we're detained;

15:34.400 --> 15:36.530 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
we cannot leave."

15:36.530 --> 15:39.530 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
It was a very regimented place.

15:39.530 --> 15:42.470 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Children were walking,
and there was this one child,

15:42.470 --> 15:44.070 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and he was crying.

15:44.070 --> 15:48.770 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
So, I asked the children,
"How come I saw a child crying,

15:48.770 --> 15:50.230 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and nobody was addressing
that child?"

15:50.230 --> 15:54.130 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
And they said that they were not
allowed to talk to one another

15:54.130 --> 15:55.770 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
most of the time,

15:55.770 --> 15:57.670 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and then they're not allowed
to touch one another,

15:57.670 --> 15:59.800 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and they're not allowed
to offer comfort.

15:59.800 --> 16:02.770 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
So, we tend to see teenagers
as mini-adults.

16:02.770 --> 16:03.930 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
They're not adults.

16:03.930 --> 16:06.300 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
They cannot regulate
their own emotions.

16:06.300 --> 16:08.930 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
They don't think of the future
as we do.

16:08.930 --> 16:12.300 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
They think, "This is going
to last forever."

16:12.300 --> 16:15.200 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
The longer they stay in these
detention conditions,

16:15.200 --> 16:18.470 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
the more they deteriorate
psychologically.

16:20.700 --> 16:23.230 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> GIRL:

16:30.700 --> 16:33.730 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN:

16:34.830 --> 16:37.900 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> GIRL:

16:41.200 --> 16:43.130 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN AND GIRL:

16:45.870 --> 16:50.470 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> GIRL:

17:01.930 --> 17:04.000 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> The security around any of
our shelters

17:04.000 --> 17:07.400 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
is more to keep people out
than to keep people in.

17:07.400 --> 17:09.070 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Especially with some of the
older children, you know,

17:09.070 --> 17:11.400 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
these aren't secure facilities
that are impossible

17:11.400 --> 17:12.900 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
to get out of.

17:12.900 --> 17:15.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
The overwhelming majority,
the near-unanimous number

17:15.100 --> 17:18.700 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
of children in our care,
are grateful.

17:18.700 --> 17:20.670 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: There are now
approximately

17:20.670 --> 17:24.430 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
170 HHS shelter programs
for migrant kids

17:24.430 --> 17:27.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
across the country, from small
foster-care sites

17:27.630 --> 17:31.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
to places like Homestead.

17:31.100 --> 17:34.900 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
HHS houses the youngest
migrants, infants and toddlers,

17:34.900 --> 17:39.130 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
in a handful of facilities they
call "tender-age" shelters.

17:39.130 --> 17:42.330 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
We were recently given rare
access to this shelter

17:42.330 --> 17:46.070 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
holding babies and teenage
mothers in San Benito, Texas.

17:46.070 --> 17:47.570 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> This is our busy hallway.

17:47.570 --> 17:50.600 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
There's constantly children
playing, nursing, eating.

17:50.600 --> 17:53.900 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Melissa Aguilar is the
director of shelter programs

17:53.900 --> 17:56.330 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
for Comprehensive
Health Services,

17:56.330 --> 17:59.130 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
a private company
that runs the shelter.

17:59.130 --> 18:01.730 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> We focus on zero to 17.

18:01.730 --> 18:03.230 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
So, we have mothers in care.

18:03.230 --> 18:06.230 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
We have the capacity to service
pregnant teenagers,

18:06.230 --> 18:08.600 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and they can also care
for their babies here.

18:08.600 --> 18:10.730 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
A staff said it earlier today,
and she said it best,

18:10.730 --> 18:12.070 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
that "the children
are borrowed."

18:12.070 --> 18:14.430 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
They're borrowed for-for
our purpose, right?

18:14.430 --> 18:16.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
So, a lot of times,
when something is borrowed,

18:16.100 --> 18:17.870 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
you take care of them better
than you would

18:17.870 --> 18:19.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
something that is your own.

18:19.630 --> 18:21.870 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: The company runs five
other shelters,

18:21.870 --> 18:23.670 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
including Homestead.

18:23.670 --> 18:25.470 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
And among its leadership is

18:25.470 --> 18:27.870 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
former White House Chief
of Staff John Kelly,

18:27.870 --> 18:30.000 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
who'd backed the policy
of separating kids

18:30.000 --> 18:33.770 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
from their families
at the border.

18:33.770 --> 18:36.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Over the past year, the
government has paid CHS

18:36.630 --> 18:39.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
nearly $300 million.

18:39.630 --> 18:42.670 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
By its very definition,
when you're for-profit,

18:42.670 --> 18:45.530 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
your job as a company
is to make a profit.

18:45.530 --> 18:47.930 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
So, some people might say, then,

18:47.930 --> 18:51.300 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
isn't there then an incentive
to detain kids?

18:51.300 --> 18:54.000 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> There is a profit,
there is a price incentive,

18:54.000 --> 18:56.370 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
but it's not a detention
incentive.

18:56.370 --> 18:58.930 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
The-the question about is there
incentive to detain children--

18:58.930 --> 19:00.370 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
absolutely not.

19:00.370 --> 19:02.000 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
And I think that it's so
important for everybody

19:02.000 --> 19:04.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
to understand that we're not
detaining children.

19:04.630 --> 19:06.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
We're not separating children.

19:06.100 --> 19:07.600 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
We're caring for children.

19:07.600 --> 19:12.930 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> BURKE: Morally, ethically, is
it okay for a for-profit company

19:12.930 --> 19:17.470 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
to make money from holding
children in mass facilities

19:17.470 --> 19:19.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
that they cannot leave?

19:19.100 --> 19:20.530 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> They're not the ones
determining

19:20.530 --> 19:22.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
what kids are coming there,

19:22.100 --> 19:24.300 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
they don't really have as much
say over who stays there.

19:24.300 --> 19:26.530 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
We can move kids in an out
if we so desire.

19:26.530 --> 19:32.070 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Am I personally opposed to, you
know, a for-profit company?

19:32.070 --> 19:34.800 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I've thought about that
question, and honestly, I'm not.

19:34.800 --> 19:36.830 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
And at the end of the day,
when you get down

19:36.830 --> 19:39.500 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
at the shelter level, you know,
you're basically talking about

19:39.500 --> 19:42.070 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
just a bunch of social workers,
child-welfare experts,

19:42.070 --> 19:45.030 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
who just want to help care
for the kids.

19:45.030 --> 19:47.370 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> We know from the American
Academy of Pediatrics

19:47.370 --> 19:49.200 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
that there's no amount of time

19:49.200 --> 19:51.700 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
that it's safe for children
to be detained.

19:51.700 --> 19:55.170 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
We know definitively that
detention harms children.

19:55.170 --> 19:58.000 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
That every single day that
children are there,

19:58.000 --> 20:00.770 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
those impacts compound.

20:00.770 --> 20:04.300 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Recently, HHS's
internal investigator

20:04.300 --> 20:05.700 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
looked into the issue.

20:05.700 --> 20:08.030 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> MENDOZA: They took a look
at the shelter system

20:08.030 --> 20:10.670 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and concluded
in their own report

20:10.670 --> 20:13.530 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
that the mental-health needs of
these kids was not being met.

20:13.530 --> 20:17.500 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Some kids were getting stressed
out to the extreme,

20:17.500 --> 20:19.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
inflicting self-harm,

20:19.270 --> 20:23.000 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
becoming extremely withdrawn
and depressed.

20:23.000 --> 20:25.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Beyond the
mental-health impacts,

20:25.100 --> 20:27.100 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
there have also been documented
cases

20:27.100 --> 20:31.070 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
of physical and sexual abuse
at some HHS shelters--

20:31.070 --> 20:33.600 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and the A.P. reported
that children and families

20:33.600 --> 20:37.670 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
are now suing the U.S. for
hundreds of millions of dollars.

20:37.670 --> 20:39.670 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
♪ ♪

20:39.670 --> 20:43.900 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
As for Martin, after almost
three weeks in detention,

20:43.900 --> 20:48.170 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
he found out he would finally be
going home.

20:48.170 --> 20:52.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> On a Saturday night,
I was going to sleep,

20:52.270 --> 20:55.770 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and they woke me up, like,
around 10:00, 10:30.

20:55.770 --> 21:01.770 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
And they're like,
"You're getting to leave."

21:01.770 --> 21:05.030 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> WOMAN:

21:30.170 --> 21:32.500 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> When I saw them, I just,
like, ran to her

21:32.500 --> 21:34.200 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and got to hug her.

21:34.200 --> 21:38.870 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I just stared at them,
didn't know what to do.

21:38.870 --> 21:41.200 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Before I didn't really,
like, miss my mom,

21:41.200 --> 21:44.670 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
'cause I got to see her
every day.

21:44.670 --> 21:46.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I didn't feel like there would
be that empty space

21:46.630 --> 21:51.830 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
where you actually need
that hug from your mom.

21:51.830 --> 21:55.800 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
The first two weeks,
I-I didn't really get to sleep.

21:55.800 --> 22:00.830 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I was still, like, confused
about what was happening.

22:00.830 --> 22:05.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I wasn't really stable.

22:05.270 --> 22:09.700 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I'm still scared that something
bad could happen.

22:09.700 --> 22:12.330 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Like, I don't feel safe anymore.

22:12.330 --> 22:15.200 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
♪ ♪

22:18.230 --> 22:20.130 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> XIOMARA:

22:25.300 --> 22:28.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: After nearly
four months,

22:28.100 --> 22:31.800 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Xiomara was finally recognized
as Jarin's aunt by HHS.

22:33.800 --> 22:37.570 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> JARIN:

22:50.000 --> 22:51.300 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> XIOMARA:

23:05.570 --> 23:08.100 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> XIOMARA:

23:11.030 --> 23:13.530 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> WOMAN (on phone):

23:20.800 --> 23:22.430 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
♪ ♪

23:23.630 --> 23:28.300 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> XIOMARA:

23:49.600 --> 23:54.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
(people speaking Spanish
in background)

23:54.270 --> 23:57.170 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> JARIN:

24:04.270 --> 24:06.070 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
(applause)

24:06.070 --> 24:07.630 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> Your conscious mind
may not remember,

24:07.630 --> 24:09.230 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
but your body remembers.

24:09.230 --> 24:10.900 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
Your brain remembers.

24:10.900 --> 24:15.030 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
And maybe that child, at that
moment, says, "I'm okay."

24:15.030 --> 24:17.800 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
But later on he might be in
a situation that is scary,

24:17.800 --> 24:19.300 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
and then he might freeze.

24:19.300 --> 24:23.800 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
And he doesn't know why.

24:23.800 --> 24:26.730 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
♪ ♪

24:26.730 --> 24:30.900 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: We visited Martin two
months after he came home.

24:30.900 --> 24:33.270 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
He and his family asked to see
the footage

24:33.270 --> 24:35.770 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
of the moment when
he was first detained.

24:37.470 --> 24:39.230 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> (on recording): Listen,
I'm at a check-and-stop

24:39.230 --> 24:41.430 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
here in Texas.

24:41.430 --> 24:43.830 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I got six subjects, one of
them's got a New York state...

24:43.830 --> 24:45.670 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Were you surprised
when they got

24:45.670 --> 24:47.570 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
the Border Patrol on the phone?
>> Yes.

24:47.570 --> 24:51.900 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
I just didn't know, like, what
to say or how to react.

24:51.900 --> 24:53.500 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
(police chatter on recording)

24:54.630 --> 24:57.400 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN:

24:57.400 --> 24:58.700 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> No, it's okay.

24:58.700 --> 25:01.430 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Okay.

25:01.430 --> 25:05.870 align:left position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> It's just... constant thing
I wish, like, it never happened.

25:05.870 --> 25:06.870 position:10%,start line:85% size:80%
>> ALTAN: Mm-hmm.

